<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 05 at 3:13PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Band of moderate snow showers to impact portions of North
Central and Central Montana through the late afternoon hours...
At 3 pm, a band of moderate snow showers extended from near Cut
Bank southeast through Toole, southwest Liberty, northeast
Pondera, southwest Chouteau, and western Fergus Counties. This
band will continue to move slowly south through 5 pm.
Accumulations will likely remain less than one inch from these
showers, but they may reduce visibility to less than one mile in
some areas due to blowing snow, and they may cause roads to become
slick in spots.
Be careful on the roads this afternoon, and be prepared for
rapidly changing weather and road conditions.</description>
